    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling outing today, led by **Kyle Tucker** (80.85) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.10). **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a favorable matchup against Jack Leiter, bolstered by a 0.372 xwOBA and wind conditions working in his favor at the park. **Jackson Merrill** is a priority play against Ryan Feltner; he enjoys a massive 15% SP skill advantage and, crucially, faces a slow-delivering pitcher that offers a 100% stolen base probability boost\u2014a critical factor given our mandate to prioritize speed. Meanwhile, **Gunnar Henderson** (70.88) remains a foundational piece despite facing the talented Logan Webb, as his top-of-the-order positioning and a significant platoon advantage help offset the tough matchup.\n\nPlatoon edges are driving much of our secondary production today. **Luis Robert Jr.** (62.04) and **Andy Pages** (64.55) are both recommended starts, with **Luis Robert Jr.** enjoying a 14% platoon boost against J.P. France and **Andy Pages** finding value in a wind-aided environment. The most difficult personnel decision involved leaving **Marcell Ozuna** (52.05) on the bench; while he maintained a respectable score, his efficiency simply didn't eclipse the high-speed or platoon-advantaged profiles of our starting outfield and middle infielders. We are monitoring lineup confirmations for **Gunnar Henderson**, **Andy Pages**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Jackson Merrill**, as any drastic shifts in their projected batting order could compress their efficiency scores against these respective rotations. Note that while **Heliot Ramos** (57.30) draws a tough assignment against Chris Bassitt, the 16% park factor keeps him above our marginal threshold, though he remains a player to watch if the wind shifts.",
